law.text:
Any local government electing to enact a nuisance code and enforce violations of the nuisance code as civil violations shall enact an ordinance or ordinances which:
Establish the acts, actions, behavior, or conditions which constitute violations;
Establish reasonable standards and procedures for the enforcement of the nuisance code;
Provide for the establishment of a hearing board and hearing officers and the procedures to be followed by the hearing board and hearing officers;
Delegate responsibility for enforcement of the nuisance code to an agency or department of the local government; and
Establish penalties to be imposed upon persons determined to have violated the nuisance code.
